The Department of Petroleum Resources (DPR) said 16 trucks of fuel expected to be delivered to Adamawa State has been diverted by two unknown companies. The controller of DPR Adamawa and Taraba, Muhammed Alaku stated this Tuesday during a monitoring tour of fuel stations in five different local government areas of the state. He said Kakumi Nigeria limited has lifted 11 trucks of fuel and Kavamchi oil lifted five trucks of petroleum products which have not been delivered to the state. Alaku said DPR taken measures to track defaulters. “We have sealed two filling stations in Taraba  and one filling station in Adamawa for failure to comply to regulations and will continue to clamp down on any illegal activity aimed at frustrating the efforts of the federal government in making the product available to Nigerians.” He stated.